---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About TRST.com | Our Mission"
  description="TRST.com is the definitive authority on the invisible infrastructure of the digital economy. Our mission: map the technologies and protocols making modern trust possible."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="border-b border-border py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-mint uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">About</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6">
          Defining the<br />
          <span class="text-gradient">Trust Economy</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-ghost/70 leading-relaxed">
          TRST.com is the definitive authority on the invisible infrastructure of the digital economy.
          We map the technologies, frameworks, and protocols that make modern commerce, identity, and
          AI interaction possible.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Our Mission</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-ghost/70 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            In 2026, the digital economy operates on the premise of trust. Every transaction, every login,
            every AI interaction rests on a foundation of protocols and systems most people never see.
          </p>
          <p>
            TRST was created to make that invisible infrastructure visible. We believe that the architects
            of the next digital era—developers, security professionals, product leaders, and policymakers—need
            a comprehensive, technically rigorous reference for the trust layer.
          </p>
          <p>
            We provide independent analysis of the technologies, vendors, and standards shaping how
            humans and machines establish, verify, and maintain trust in digital environments.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Technological Analysis',
            desc: 'We assess platforms based on cryptographic security, user privacy, scalability, and interoperability.',
            icon: '🔬',
          },
          {
            title: 'Independent Perspective',
            desc: 'No vendor relationships influence our Trust Scores. Our ratings are based on public technical analysis.',
            icon: '⚖️',
          },
          {
            title: 'Forward-Looking',
            desc: 'We focus on the 2026 and beyond trust stack—including AI agent identity, ZK proofs, and self-sovereign systems.',
            icon: '🔭',
          },
          {
            title: 'Developer-First',
            desc: 'Our content is designed for the engineers and architects building the next generation of trust infrastructure.',
            icon: '💻',
          },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="card p-5 flex gap-4">
            <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">{item.icon}</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-ghost mb-1">{item.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem We Solve -->
  <section class="border-t border-border bg-slate/20 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-mint uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 text-center">The Problem</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Why TRST Exists</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-ghost/70 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The explosion of generative AI in 2025–2026 introduced a fundamental crisis of trust. When
          synthetic media is indistinguishable from authentic content, when AI agents can impersonate
          humans at scale, and when the "cost of deception" approaches zero—the systems that verify
          what is real become critical infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p>
          Yet the trust infrastructure landscape is fragmented, rapidly evolving, and poorly documented
          for the practitioners who need to build with it. TRST fills that gap: a single authoritative
          reference for the technologies that answer the question "can we trust this?"
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-sm text-ghost border border-border rounded-lg p-4 bg-midnight">
          "Security is about keeping people out. Trust is about letting the right people in."
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 border-t border-border">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10 text-center">Our Principles</h2>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {[
        { num: '01', title: 'Cryptography First', desc: 'Trust must be mathematically provable, not merely assumed.' },
        { num: '02', title: 'Privacy by Design', desc: 'Verification should reveal minimum necessary information.' },
        { num: '03', title: 'Decentralization', desc: 'Trust systems with single points of failure are not trustworthy.' },
        { num: '04', title: 'Open Standards', desc: 'Interoperable standards prevent lock-in and enable ecosystem trust.' },
        { num: '05', title: 'Human Sovereignty', desc: 'Individuals must retain control over their digital identity.' },
        { num: '06', title: 'AI Accountability', desc: 'Autonomous agents must be as accountable as human actors.' },
      ].map(p => (
        <div class="card p-6">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-mint mb-3">{p.num}</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-ghost mb-2">{p.title}</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">{p.desc}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Disclaimer -->
  <section class="border-t border-border py-12 bg-slate/20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-xs text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-ghost/50">Disclaimer:</strong> TRST.com provides technological analysis and is not a legal or security auditing firm.
        Trust Scores are based on publicly available technical analysis and do not constitute endorsements.
        This site complies with GDPR-v3 and CCPA-2026 data handling standards.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Start Exploring</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/infrastructure" class="px-6 py-3 bg-mint text-midnight font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-mint-dim transition-colors">
          View the Trust Map
        </a>
        <a href="/newsletter" class="px-6 py-3 border border-border text-ghost/80 font-semibold rounded-lg hover:border-mint hover:text-mint transition-colors">
          Subscribe to The Trust Signal
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
